Sec. 63.034. REFUSAL OR REVOCATION OF PERMIT. Following notice
and a hearing, the service may revoke, suspend, annul, or amend an
existing permit or may refuse to issue a permit if it finds that the
permittee or applicant has:
(1) been convicted of a crime for which a permit may be
revoked, suspended, annulled, amended, or refused under Chapter 53,
Occupations Code;
(2) refused or after notice failed to comply with this
chapter and rules adopted under this chapter; or
Statute text rendered on: 8/6/2022

- 388 -

AGRICULTURE CODE

(3) used fraudulent or deceptive practices in attempting
evasion of this chapter or a rule adopted under this chapter.
